# PromoteObstacle — convert a transient tracker observation into a
# user-validated permanent keepout polygon.
#
# After the obstacle-tracker decouple (2026-05-07), map_server no longer
# auto-mirrors /obstacle_tracker/obstacles into the classification layer
# or obstacle_polygons_. The tracker output is for monitoring only. To
# turn one of those tracker observations (or any user-drawn polygon)
# into a permanent keepout, the GUI calls this service.
#
# Effects:
#   * The polygon is appended to the target area's obstacles list.
#   * Cells inside become NO_GO_ZONE in the classification layer.
#   * The keepout mask is rebuilt so Smac/Nav2 see the polygon as lethal.
#   * The area YAML is persisted so the obstacle survives restart.
#   * Reachability BFS is re-run for the area (DEAD recompute).
#
# Either obstacle_id or polygon must be set:
#   * obstacle_id != 0  → look up the tracked obstacle with this id in
#                          the most recent /obstacle_tracker/obstacles
#                          snapshot (cached in map_server) and use its
#                          polygon. Easiest GUI path: "promote tracker #N".
#   * obstacle_id == 0  → use the polygon field directly. Free-form
#                          path for user-drawn keepouts.

# Target area (must be a mowing area, not a navigation area).
uint32 area_index

# Either look up the tracker observation by id (recommended), or supply
# a polygon directly. If both are set, polygon wins.
uint32 obstacle_id
geometry_msgs/Polygon polygon
---
bool success
string message
